schleifenbauerDatabusMIB.contactinfo: Schleifenbauer Engineering Alain Schuermans Chief Technology Officer Turnhoutseweg 22 5541 NX Reusel The Netherlands t. +31 73 5230256 f. +31 73 5212383 alain@schleifenbauer.eu www.schleifenbauer.eu
schleifenbauerDatabusMIB.description: This MIB describes the SNMP functions of network enabled databus devices. Copyright (c) 2016 by Schleifenbauer Holding BV

DeciValue.name: DeciValue
DeciValue.description: Data type for reporting generic measurements associated with environmental sensors. If the underlying hardware sensor indicates 21.1 degrees Celsius, then the SNMP agent will report a value of 2110 DeciValue.

KiloWattHour.name: KiloWattHour
KiloWattHour.description: Data type for reporting measurements associated with energy accumulation sensors. If the underlying hardware sensor indicates 1 kWh, then the SNMP agent will report a value of 1 kWh.

DeciAmpere.name: DeciAmpere
DeciAmpere.description: Data type for reporting measurements and thresholds associated with current sensors. If the underlying hardware sensor indicates 1.1 A, then the SNMP agent will report a value of 110 DeciAmpere.

DeciCelsius.name: DeciCelsius
DeciCelsius.description: Data type for reporting sensor readings associated with temperature sensors. If the underlying hardware sensor indicates 20.1 degrees Celsius, then the SNMP agent will report a value of 2010 DeciCelsius.

DeciPercent.name: DeciPercent
DeciPercent.description: Data type for reporting calculated percentages. If the calculated percentage is 98.3%, then the SNMP agent will report a value of 9830 DeciPercent.

DeciVolt.name: DeciVolt
DeciVolt.description: Data type for reporting measurements and thresholds associated with voltage sensors. If the underlying hardware sensor indicates 231.1 V, then the SNMP agent will report a value of 23110 DeciVolt.

sdbMgmtStsDevices.name: sdbMgmtStsDevices
sdbMgmtStsDevices.description: The number of devices on the databus.

sdbMgmtStsAddressableDevices.name: sdbMgmtStsAddressableDevices
sdbMgmtStsAddressableDevices.description: The number of devices on the databus addressable by snmp.

sdbMgmtStsNewDevices.name: sdbMgmtStsNewDevices
sdbMgmtStsNewDevices.description: The number of new devices on the databus.

sdbMgmtStsDuplicateDevices.name: sdbMgmtStsDuplicateDevices
sdbMgmtStsDuplicateDevices.description: The number of duplicate devices on the databus.

sdbMgmtStsRingState.name: sdbMgmtStsRingState
sdbMgmtStsRingState.description: If the device is in a bridge-like mode, this will indicate the actual state of the databus.

sdbMgmtStsRingBreachIndex.name: sdbMgmtStsRingBreachIndex
sdbMgmtStsRingBreachIndex.description: Indicates the breach index if the current state of the data bus is open. If the data bus is closed this has no meaning.

sdbMgmtCtrlScan.name: sdbMgmtCtrlScan
sdbMgmtCtrlScan.description: Perform a bus scan. To verify if scanning is completed the value of this object can be read. During the bus scan the value remains 1. When the bus scan completed the value will be 0.

sdbMgmtCtrlRenumberAllFromN.name: sdbMgmtCtrlRenumberAllFromN
sdbMgmtCtrlRenumberAllFromN.description: Renumber all devices on the databus. If set to 0 all units will be set to 0. If set to another value, all units will be numbered in sequence starting from the value set.

sdbMgmtCtrlRenumberZeros.name: sdbMgmtCtrlRenumberZeros
sdbMgmtCtrlRenumberZeros.description: Renumber all devices on the databus having address 0. Renumbering will be done in sequence. The sequence starts with the highest address found on the databus.

sdbMgmtCtrlDevicesTable.name: sdbMgmtCtrlDevicesTable
sdbMgmtCtrlDevicesTable.description: A table containing information of devices connected to the databus. The number of entries is given by the value of sdbMgmtStsDevices.

sdbMgmtCtrlDevicesEntry.name: sdbMgmtCtrlDevicesEntry
sdbMgmtCtrlDevicesEntry.description: Information entry containing objects of a particular databus device.

sdbMgmtCtrlDevIndex.name: sdbMgmtCtrlDevIndex
sdbMgmtCtrlDevIndex.description: A unique value for each device. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of sdbMgmtStsDevices with a maximum of 255. The value for each device will remain constant until the next scan is performed.

sdbMgmtCtrlDevUnitAddress.name: sdbMgmtCtrlDevUnitAddress
sdbMgmtCtrlDevUnitAddress.description: User defined address. This will be used for addressing the device on the databus.

sdbMgmtCtrlDevHardwareAddress.name: sdbMgmtCtrlDevHardwareAddress
sdbMgmtCtrlDevHardwareAddress.description: Hardware serial number. This cannot be changed. It can be used as backup unit address. format as 3 unsigned ints separated by dashes: int - int - int

sdbMgmtCtrlDevIsNew.name: sdbMgmtCtrlDevIsNew
sdbMgmtCtrlDevIsNew.description: Indication if the device is new on the databus.

sdbMgmtCtrlDevIsDuplicate.name: sdbMgmtCtrlDevIsDuplicate
sdbMgmtCtrlDevIsDuplicate.description: Indication if the device is conflicting with another device on the databus.

sdbDevIdTable.name: sdbDevIdTable
sdbDevIdTable.description: A table containing identification information of devices connected to the databus. The number of entries is given by the value of sdbMgmtStsAddressableDevices.

sdbDevIdEntry.name: sdbDevIdEntry
sdbDevIdEntry.description: Information entry containing information objects of a particular databus device.

sdbDevIdBuildNumber.name: sdbDevIdBuildNumber
sdbDevIdBuildNumber.description: Date and time the firmware was built.

sdbDevIdHardwareAddress.name: sdbDevIdHardwareAddress
sdbDevIdHardwareAddress.description: Hardware serial number. This can not be changed. It can be used as backup unit address. Format as 3 unsigned ints separated by dashes (-) e.g. 12345-54321-00000

sdbDevIdMacAddress.name: sdbDevIdMacAddress
sdbDevIdMacAddress.description: The MAC address. This can not be changed. It represents an 802 MAC address as if it were transmitted least significant bit first. Format as six groups of 2 hexadecimal digits separated by colons (:) e.g. D0:22:12:B0:00:00

sdbDevIdUnitAddress.name: sdbDevIdUnitAddress
sdbDevIdUnitAddress.description: User defined address. This will be used for addressing the device on the databus.

sdbDevIdName.name: sdbDevIdName
sdbDevIdName.description: User configurable device name or identifier.

sdbDevIdVanityTag.name: sdbDevIdVanityTag
sdbDevIdVanityTag.description: Characters to be displayed as vanity text in display.

sdbDevIdIndex.name: sdbDevIdIndex
sdbDevIdIndex.description: A unique value for each device. Its value represents the unit address of the device and is used to address individual devices in the tree. The value for each device will remain constant until the next scan is performed.

sdbDevCfTable.name: sdbDevCfTable
sdbDevCfTable.description: A table containing configuration information of devices connected to the databus. The number of entries is given by the value of sdbMgmtStsAddressableDevices.

sdbDevCfEntry.name: sdbDevCfEntry
sdbDevCfEntry.description: Configuration entry containing configuration objects of a particular databus device.

sdbDevCfPhases.name: sdbDevCfPhases
sdbDevCfPhases.description: Number of phases for input metering.

sdbDevCfOutletsTotal.name: sdbDevCfOutletsTotal
sdbDevCfOutletsTotal.description: Total number of outlets including hardwired without switch/metered modules.

sdbDevCfOutletsSwitched.name: sdbDevCfOutletsSwitched
sdbDevCfOutletsSwitched.description: Number of switched outlets. If outlet numbering is non-contiguous its the highest outlet number.

sdbDevCfOutletsMetered.name: sdbDevCfOutletsMetered
sdbDevCfOutletsMetered.description: Number of metered outlets. If outlet numbering is non-contiguous its the highest outlet number.

sdbDevCfMaximumLoad.name: sdbDevCfMaximumLoad
sdbDevCfMaximumLoad.description: Maximum rated load of device per phase

sdbDevSsTable.name: sdbDevSsTable
sdbDevSsTable.description: A table containing system status information of devices connected to the databus. The number of entries is given by the value of sdbMgmtStsAddressableDevices.

sdbDevSsEntry.name: sdbDevSsEntry
sdbDevSsEntry.description: System status entry containing system status objects of a particular databus device.

sdbDevSsDeviceStatusCode.name: sdbDevSsDeviceStatusCode
sdbDevSsDeviceStatusCode.description: Returns an internal status or error code. A value of 0 means OK. If not 0 it can be any of the following codes. Multiple status codes can be active at the same time. The value will be the sum of the active status codes. 1 = alert flagged 2 = settings(s) initialized 4 = power-on reset 8 = external reset 16 = watchdog timer caused reset 32 = brownout detected 64 = controller error 128 = slave module was reset

sdbDevSsTemperatureAlert.name: sdbDevSsTemperatureAlert
sdbDevSsTemperatureAlert.description: An alert has been raised due to temperature exceeding treshhold. 0 = no alert 1 = internal temperature sensor 2 = external temperature sensor

sdbDevSsInputCurrentAlert.name: sdbDevSsInputCurrentAlert
sdbDevSsInputCurrentAlert.description: An alert has been raised due to current exceeding treshhold. The value indicates the exceeding phase. 0 = no alert.

sdbDevSsOutletCurrentAlert.name: sdbDevSsOutletCurrentAlert
sdbDevSsOutletCurrentAlert.description: An alert has been raised due to current exceeding treshhold. The value indicates the exceeding outlet. 0 = no alert.

sdbDevSsInputVoltageAlert.name: sdbDevSsInputVoltageAlert
sdbDevSsInputVoltageAlert.description: An alert has been raised due to a voltage dip. The value indicates the dipped phase. 0 = no alert.

sdbDevSsOutletCurrentDropAlert.name: sdbDevSsOutletCurrentDropAlert
sdbDevSsOutletCurrentDropAlert.description: An alert has been raised due to the current of a metered outlet suddenly dropping to near zero, possibly indicating a blown fuse. The value indicates the dropped outlet. 0 = no alert.

sdbDevSsInputCurrentDropAlert.name: sdbDevSsInputCurrentDropAlert
sdbDevSsInputCurrentDropAlert.description: An alert has been raised due to the current of a metered input suddenly dropping to near zero, possibly indicating a blown fuse. The value indicates the dropped phase. 0 = no alert.

sdbDevSsSensorChangeAlert.name: sdbDevSsSensorChangeAlert
sdbDevSsSensorChangeAlert.description: An alert has been raised due to a change in the number of sensors. The value indicates the previous amount of sensors.

sdbDevSsOutletVoltageDropAlert.name: sdbDevSsOutletVoltageDropAlert
sdbDevSsOutletVoltageDropAlert.description: An alert has been raised due to voltage drop on this outlet. The value indicates the first failed outlet.

sdbDevRsTable.name: sdbDevRsTable
sdbDevRsTable.description: A table providing reset capabilities to devices connected to the databus. The number of entries is given by the value of sdbMgmtStsAddressableDevices.

sdbDevRsEntry.name: sdbDevRsEntry
sdbDevRsEntry.description: Reset entry providing reset objects of a particular databus device.

sdbDevRsReboot.name: sdbDevRsReboot
sdbDevRsReboot.description: Warm reboot/reset of device controller. NOTE: this will have NO effect on outlet status!

sdbDevRsResetAlerts.name: sdbDevRsResetAlerts
sdbDevRsResetAlerts.description: Reset all alert signals and device status code.

sdbDevRsZeroInputKWhSubtotal.name: sdbDevRsZeroInputKWhSubtotal
sdbDevRsZeroInputKWhSubtotal.description: Reset of all input kWh subtotal counters to zero.

sdbDevRsZeroOutletKWhSubtotal.name: sdbDevRsZeroOutletKWhSubtotal
sdbDevRsZeroOutletKWhSubtotal.description: Reset of all outlet kWh subtotal counter to zero.

sdbDevRsResetPeaksAndDips.name: sdbDevRsResetPeaksAndDips
sdbDevRsResetPeaksAndDips.description: Reset all peak and dip values to zero.

sdbDevStTable.name: sdbDevStTable
sdbDevStTable.description: A table containing setting information of devices connected to the databus. The number of entries is given by the value of sdbMgmtStsAddressableDevices.

sdbDevStEntry.name: sdbDevStEntry
sdbDevStEntry.description: Setting entry containing settings objects of a particular databus device.

sdbDevStAutoResetAlerts.name: sdbDevStAutoResetAlerts
sdbDevStAutoResetAlerts.description: Auto reset alerts configuration. If set to 0 the auto reset alerts feature is disabled. If set to a value greater then 0, the auto reset alerts feature is enabled and alerts will get cleared after the configured amount of seconds since the last alert condition have passed.

sdbDevStExtendedNames.name: sdbDevStExtendedNames
sdbDevStExtendedNames.description: Use original or longer names for inputs, outlets and sensors.

sdbDevStPeakDuration.name: sdbDevStPeakDuration
sdbDevStPeakDuration.description: Amount of ms a current peak should last before an alert is raised.

sdbDevStFixedOutletDelay.name: sdbDevStFixedOutletDelay
sdbDevStFixedOutletDelay.description: Minimal delay between two successive relay switches in milliseconds. Minimal delay is 100 ms. Will always be respected!

sdbDevStPowerSaverMode.name: sdbDevStPowerSaverMode
sdbDevStPowerSaverMode.description: Set backlight on time in seconds. 0 keeps display always on. Note that keeping the backlight on may decrease luminosity over time.

sdbDevStMaximumTemperature.name: sdbDevStMaximumTemperature
sdbDevStMaximumTemperature.description: Maximum temperature threshold An alert will be generated whenever the temperature is above this value. Zero means disabled.

sdbDevStLocalAlertReset.name: sdbDevStLocalAlertReset
sdbDevStLocalAlertReset.description: Allow alerts to be reset locally on device by pushing one of the buttons.

sdbDevStCurrentDropDetection.name: sdbDevStCurrentDropDetection
sdbDevStCurrentDropDetection.description: Enables the current drop detection function.

sdbDevInTable.name: sdbDevInTable
sdbDevInTable.description: A table containing information of inputs of devices connected to the databus.

sdbDevInEntry.name: sdbDevInEntry
sdbDevInEntry.description: Inputs entry containing objects of an input of a particular databus device. Note that this table has two indexes. sdbDevIdIndex to identify a particular device and sdbDevInIndex to identify a particular input of the device identified by sdbDevIdIndex.

sdbDevInIndex.name: sdbDevInIndex
sdbDevInIndex.description: A unique value for each input. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of sdbDevCfPhases.

sdbDevInKWhTotal.name: sdbDevInKWhTotal
sdbDevInKWhTotal.description: Total kWh value of an input. This value can not be reset.

sdbDevInKWhSubtotal.name: sdbDevInKWhSubtotal
sdbDevInKWhSubtotal.description: Subtotal kWh value of an input. This value can be reset.

sdbDevInPowerFactor.name: sdbDevInPowerFactor
sdbDevInPowerFactor.description: Power factor of input. The power factor of an AC power system is defined as the ratio of the real or active power to the apparent power and is a number between 0 and 1. This value is expressed as a percentage between 0% and 100%.

sdbDevInPeakCurrent.name: sdbDevInPeakCurrent
sdbDevInPeakCurrent.description: Peak apparent, RMS current. Highest value since last reset of the alerts.

sdbDevInMinVoltage.name: sdbDevInMinVoltage
sdbDevInMinVoltage.description: RMS voltage dip. Lowest value since reset of alerts.

sdbDevInMaxAmps.name: sdbDevInMaxAmps
sdbDevInMaxAmps.description: Maximum current per input phase. Should last at least sdbDevStPeakDuration ms before triggering an alert.

sdbDevInCTRatio.name: sdbDevInCTRatio
sdbDevInCTRatio.description: The multiplier to use for the input CTs.

sdbDevInName.name: sdbDevInName
sdbDevInName.description: User configurable naming of inputs or phases.

sdbDevInZeroKWhSubtotal.name: sdbDevInZeroKWhSubtotal
sdbDevInZeroKWhSubtotal.description: Reset input kWh subtotal counter of a single input to zero.

sdbDevOutTable.name: sdbDevOutTable
sdbDevOutTable.description: A table containing information of outlets of devices connected to the databus.

sdbDevOutEntry.name: sdbDevOutEntry
sdbDevOutEntry.description: Outlets entry containing objects of an outlet of a particular databus device. Note that this table has two indexes. sdbDevIdIndex to identify a particular device and sdbDevOutIndex to identify a particular outlet of the device identified by sdbDevIdIndex.

sdbDevOutIndex.name: sdbDevOutIndex
sdbDevOutIndex.description: A unique value for each outlet. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of sdbDevCfOutletsTotal.

sdbDevOutName.name: sdbDevOutName
sdbDevOutName.description: User configurable naming of individual outlets.

sdbDevOutMtTable.name: sdbDevOutMtTable
sdbDevOutMtTable.description: A table containing information of metered outlets of devices connected to the databus.

sdbDevOutMtEntry.name: sdbDevOutMtEntry
sdbDevOutMtEntry.description: Metered outlets entry containing objects of a metered outlet of a particular databus device. Note that this table has two indexes. sdbDevIdIndex to identify a particular device and sdbDevOutMtIndex to identify a particular outlet of the device identified by sdbDevIdIndex.

sdbDevOutMtIndex.name: sdbDevOutMtIndex
sdbDevOutMtIndex.description: A unique value for each outlet. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of sdbDevCfOutletsMetered.

sdbDevOutMtKWhTotal.name: sdbDevOutMtKWhTotal
sdbDevOutMtKWhTotal.description: Total kWh value of an outlet. This value can not be reset.

sdbDevOutMtKWhSubtotal.name: sdbDevOutMtKWhSubtotal
sdbDevOutMtKWhSubtotal.description: Subotal kWh value of an outlet. This value can be reset.

sdbDevOutMtPowerFactor.name: sdbDevOutMtPowerFactor
sdbDevOutMtPowerFactor.description: Power factor of outlet. The power factor of an AC power system is defined as the ratio of the real or active power to the apparent power and is a number between 0 and 1. This number is expressed as a percentage between 0% and 100%.

sdbDevOutMtPeakCurrent.name: sdbDevOutMtPeakCurrent
sdbDevOutMtPeakCurrent.description: Peak apparent, RMS current. Highest value since last reset of the alerts.

sdbDevOutMtMaxAmps.name: sdbDevOutMtMaxAmps
sdbDevOutMtMaxAmps.description: Maximum current per outlet. Should last at least sdbDevStPeakDuration ms before triggering an alert.

sdbDevOutMtCTRatio.name: sdbDevOutMtCTRatio
sdbDevOutMtCTRatio.description: The multiplier to use for the outlet CTs.

sdbDevOutSwTable.name: sdbDevOutSwTable
sdbDevOutSwTable.description: A table containing information of switched outlets of devices connected to the databus.

sdbDevOutSwEntry.name: sdbDevOutSwEntry
sdbDevOutSwEntry.description: Switched outlets entry containing objects of a switched outlet of a particular databus device. Note that this table has two indexes. sdbDevIdIndex to identify a particular device and sdbDevOutSwIndex to identify a particular outlet of the device identified by sdbDevIdIndex.

sdbDevOutSwIndex.name: sdbDevOutSwIndex
sdbDevOutSwIndex.description: A unique value for each outlet. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of sdbDevCfOutletsSwitched.

sdbDevOutSwCurrentState.name: sdbDevOutSwCurrentState
sdbDevOutSwCurrentState.description: The actual state of the outlet relay. Note that Writing is only effective after setting sdbDevOutSwUnlock.

sdbDevOutSwScheduled.name: sdbDevOutSwScheduled
sdbDevOutSwScheduled.description: A one indicates pending activity; the switch delay has not yet expired.

sdbDevOutSwUnlock.name: sdbDevOutSwUnlock
sdbDevOutSwUnlock.description: Switching and rebooting is unlocked for 10 seconds by writing a 1.

sdbDevOutSwIndividualOutletDelay.name: sdbDevOutSwIndividualOutletDelay
sdbDevOutSwIndividualOutletDelay.description: Delay before an individual outlet switches on at power-up.

sdbDevOutSwReboot.name: sdbDevOutSwReboot
sdbDevOutSwReboot.description: Reboot outlet relay if current state is on and outlet is unlocked; The outlet will be turned on after 10 seconds.

sdbDevMeasuresTable.name: sdbDevMeasuresTable
sdbDevMeasuresTable.description: A table containing information of temperatures of devices connected to the databus.

sdbDevMeasuresEntry.name: sdbDevMeasuresEntry
sdbDevMeasuresEntry.description: Device measures entry containing temperature information objects of a particular databus device.

sdbDevMsIntTemperature.name: sdbDevMsIntTemperature
sdbDevMsIntTemperature.description: Actual internal device temperature in deg C

sdbDevMsExtTemperature.name: sdbDevMsExtTemperature
sdbDevMsExtTemperature.description: Actual external device temperature sensor in deg C.

sdbDevMsIntTemperaturePeak.name: sdbDevMsIntTemperaturePeak
sdbDevMsIntTemperaturePeak.description: Peak internal device temperature since last reset of alerts.

sdbDevMsExtTemperaturePeak.name: sdbDevMsExtTemperaturePeak
sdbDevMsExtTemperaturePeak.description: Peak external device temperature since last reset of alerts.

sdbDevSnsTable.name: sdbDevSnsTable
sdbDevSnsTable.description: A table containing information of sensors of devices connected to the databus.

sdbDevSnsEntry.name: sdbDevSnsEntry
sdbDevSnsEntry.description: Sensors entry containing objects of a sensor of a particular databus device. Note that this table has two indexes. sdbDevIdIndex to identify a particular device and sdbDevSnsIndex to identify a particular sensor of the device identified by sdbDevIdIndex.

sdbDevSnsIndex.name: sdbDevSnsIndex
sdbDevSnsIndex.description: A unique value for each sensor. Its value ranges between 1 and the value of sdbDevCfSensors.

sdbDevSnsType.name: sdbDevSnsType
sdbDevSnsType.description: Type of connected sensor. T = Temperature (C) H = Humidity (%) I = dry switch contact

sdbDevSsDeviceStatusCodeChanged.name: sdbDevSsDeviceStatusCodeChanged
sdbDevSsDeviceStatusCodeChanged.description: Device status code changed. OBJECTS { sdbDevSsDeviceStatusCode }

sdbDevSsTemperatureAlertDetected.name: sdbDevSsTemperatureAlertDetected
sdbDevSsTemperatureAlertDetected.description: Temperature alert detected. Internal temperature alert: OBJECTS { sdbDevSsTemperatureAlert, sdbDevMsIntTemperature, sdbDevMsIntTemperaturePeak } External analog temperature alert: OBJECTS { sdbDevSsTemperatureAlert, sdbDevMsExtTemperature, sdbDevMsExtTemperaturePeak } External digital temperature alert: OBJECTS { sdbDevSsTemperatureAlert, sdbDevSnsValue }

sdbDevSsInputCurrentAlertDetected.name: sdbDevSsInputCurrentAlertDetected
sdbDevSsInputCurrentAlertDetected.description: Input current alert detected. OBJECTS { sdbDevSsInputCurrentAlert, sdbDevInActualCurrent }

sdbDevSsOutletCurrentAlertDetected.name: sdbDevSsOutletCurrentAlertDetected
sdbDevSsOutletCurrentAlertDetected.description: Outlet current alert detected. OBJECTS { sdbDevSsOutletCurrentAlert, sdbDevOutMtActualCurrent }

sdbDevSsInputVoltageAlertDetected.name: sdbDevSsInputVoltageAlertDetected
sdbDevSsInputVoltageAlertDetected.description: Input voltage alert detected. OBJECTS { sdbDevSsInputVoltageAlert, sdbDevInActualVoltage }

sdbDevSsOutletCurrentDropAlertDetected.name: sdbDevSsOutletCurrentDropAlertDetected
sdbDevSsOutletCurrentDropAlertDetected.description: Outlet current drop alert detected. OBJECTS { sdbDevSsOutletCurrentDropAlert, sdbDevOutMtActualCurrent }

sdbDevSsInputCurrentDropAlertDetected.name: sdbDevSsInputCurrentDropAlertDetected
sdbDevSsInputCurrentDropAlertDetected.description: Input current drop alert detected. OBJECTS { sdbDevSsInputCurrentDropAlert, sdbDevInActualCurrent }

sdbDevSsSensorChangeAlertDetected.name: sdbDevSsSensorChangeAlertDetected
sdbDevSsSensorChangeAlertDetected.description: Sensor channel change alert detected. OBJECTS { sdbDevSsSensorChangeAlert }

sdbMgmtStsRingStateChanged.name: sdbMgmtStsRingStateChanged
sdbMgmtStsRingStateChanged.description: Ring state changed. Ring state changded to open: OBJECTS { sdbMgmtStsRingState, sdbMgmtStsRingBreachIndex } Ring state changded to closed: OBJECTS { sdbMgmtStsRingState }

sdbDevSsOutletVoltageDropAlertDetected.name: sdbDevSsOutletVoltageDropAlertDetected
sdbDevSsOutletVoltageDropAlertDetected.description: Outlet voltage drop alert detected. OBJECTS { sdbDevSsOutletVoltageDropAlert, sdbDevOutMtActualVoltage }

sdbMIBCompliance.name: sdbMIBCompliance
sdbMIBCompliance.description: The requirements for conformance to the SCHLEIFENBAUER-DATABUS-MIB.

sdbMIBDevIdGroup.name: sdbMIBDevIdGroup
sdbMIBDevIdGroup.description: A collection of objects providing identification information about the device.

sdbMIBDevCfGroup.name: sdbMIBDevCfGroup
sdbMIBDevCfGroup.description: A collection of objects providing configuration information about the device.

sdbMIBDevSsGroup.name: sdbMIBDevSsGroup
sdbMIBDevSsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing status information about the device.

sdbMIBDevRsGroup.name: sdbMIBDevRsGroup
sdbMIBDevRsGroup.description: Groups resettable attributes op the device.

sdbMIBDevStGroup.name: sdbMIBDevStGroup
sdbMIBDevStGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the actual settings about the device.

sdbMIBDevInGroup.name: sdbMIBDevInGroup
sdbMIBDevInGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the actual input measurements of the device.

sdbMIBDevOutGroup.name: sdbMIBDevOutGroup
sdbMIBDevOutGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the actual outlet measurements of the device.

sdbMIBDevOutMtGroup.name: sdbMIBDevOutMtGroup
sdbMIBDevOutMtGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the actual outlet measurements of the device.

sdbMIBDevOutSwGroup.name: sdbMIBDevOutSwGroup
sdbMIBDevOutSwGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the actual outlet measurements of the device.

sdbMIBDevSensorGroup.name: sdbMIBDevSensorGroup
sdbMIBDevSensorGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the actual environmental measurements of the device.

sdbMIBMgmtStatusGroup.name: sdbMIBMgmtStatusGroup
sdbMIBMgmtStatusGroup.description: A collection of objects providing management status information about the databus.

sdbMIBMgmtControlGroup.name: sdbMIBMgmtControlGroup
sdbMIBMgmtControlGroup.description: A collection of objects providing management control information about the databus.
